	   <tr><td colspan=2>I chose to play a DE Wizard, and have enjoyed my choice immensly. Here are some tips for those new to the wizardly profession.<br><br>1. Choose your race wisely. I chose DE for their great agility, ultravision, and their ability to hide. If you have hide, use it. It saves you from being attacked by greens while medding half the time. <br><br>2. Newbie cash. One of the hardest things when you first start to play the game is your utter lack of cash. Here are a list of things that can earn you plat fast. Stacks of Bone chips: sell to players at 2-5 plat a stack. HQ bear skin:sell to players at 20-25 plat. Greater lightstone: 8-9 plat by doing the concordance of research quest in S. RO and selling it to a vendor. All of these can be done by lvl 8 or less. Hunt these items, and you will be able to have enough to buy spells and decent starting equipment.<br><br>3. Pick your ground, and your target. Despite what people say, you can solo up to high levels. You are a Wizard, you have to be smarter than the others. You must think before you blindly attack something. Always have full mana, and be aware of your surroundings. I prefer wide open zones, full of non-aggro, non-social mobs, who run when their health is low. Root from maximum distance, and hammer away with your biggest nuke. If they break root, you should have enough time to attempt to root again. If that fails, you have to options. Go toe to toe using quick casting DD spells, hopeing that the thing tuns and runs. Or, you can shadow step, root again, or gate depending on mana. After lvl 29, you get BoF and can start kiting. I won't go into detail as it's been well covered already. Over all, be patient! When you solo, you will die on occasion. Never charge off blindly with less than full mana. I can attribute several death to trying to take that spawn before some one else did, with less than full mana.<br><br>4. Area of Effect spells are your friend! I got my first one at lvl 8, and immediatly fell in love. Being able to damage 4-6 mobs at once is an incredible ability in a group. They can take a bad multipul and turn it in the groups favor. The key is to communicate with the group. Make sure that they keep the mobs bunched together, and that they keep them well taunted. Always fire from maximum distance, and be prepared to either blast one that aggros on you, or shadowstep out of aggro range and come back to join the group.<br><br>5. At mid lvls, a Wizards job is to keep your party alive. This is not only done by dealing damage fast, but by evacing when a situation goes South. Always bind everyone near an evac point, and you will save down time. You are the master of transportation, and should never have to run more than 3 zones to get anywhere. It is better to run 3 zones with a party all alive and all together, than 1-2 zones naked into the mess that killed your party.<br><br>6. Hunting guide. Remember I chose a DE, so that heavily influenced my choices. Also keep in mind that I HATE Oasis and Ill Omen, so I ignored those zones completly.<br><br>1-4: Netekulos<br>Pretty simple, do the newbie thing. Kill decayed, get to lvl 2, kill fire beetles. Hopefully by lvl 4 you will have a stack of bone chips to sell, and can buy your lvl 4 spells.<br><br>5-7: N.Ro/EC<br>Hunted Puntar Sandfisher, Orcs, Spiders, Snakes and Bears. N. Ro is fun to, as armadilos make an excellent food source.<br><br>8-11 WC<br>Hunted Bears, Spiders, and Whisps. Also joined Derv and Befallen groups. This is where you can begin to practice those AoE spells.<br><br>12-15 Lavastorm<br>I love this zone. Pull from the entrance to Najena, so you can escape if need be. Fire Drakes, Elementals, and Dervishes are your fair of choice. Just wathc out for those imps and sprites, and remember that Elementals ARE social.<br><br>16-24 Over There (East Side)<br>Only things that aggro are the Sarnak, other then them, everything is indifferent and non-social. Loot is great too.<br><br>25-33 S. Karana<br>Hunt the Aviark village or join Split paw groups. <br><br>34-40 Over There (West Side)<br>Same as before, just bigger and tougher. <br><br>40+? <br>Velious and Kunark offer a wide variety of zones. I can't comment on them yet, as I am not that high yet. I hear Emerald Jungle is a good place to go. <br><br>Over all, be patient! You will have bad luck, down time, and fizzles that suck up your mana. The key is to suck it up, take it on the chin, and keep your wits about you. You'll be so sick of staring at your spell book by 35, that you'll see it in your sleep. Hang in there! This is a challenging, but rewarding class to play.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
