	   <tr><td colspan=2>When I started out I was a gnome wizard in the middle of steamfont mountains running around like an idiot. I found out that freeport and the commonlands will take you to 15 pretty fast. I stayed in the freeport area to lvl 3. Then went down to some ruins on the east commonlands western wall. I got in a group there to get to lvl 7. then i went on to the orc camps of east commonlands i tried to get in an orc 1 group but if that wasnt able to happen orc 2 is better than nothin. stay there to about 12 so u can get those new spells and then head over to the derv camp. Stay there to lvl 15 and head to oasis and get in an orc alley group or crocodile hunting group. those will take you to about 18 maybe 19. Once i got to 19 i soloed some crocs on the coast. Some crocodiles and deepwater caimans all conned blue which from that lvl on is good exp. As soon as you hit 20 go to Highkeep which is a small zone in the castle in highpass hold. That was the greatest exp i had ever gotten in a day of my life. I lvled 3 times there and made it to 30 from 20 in about a week. And its still descent exp now. Once u get past that first infamous hell lvl u should either go to velious ,the overthere , or PAW. Either one of these zones have good flowing exp for wizards. Oh yeah, when i say velious i mean either a Utree group in the eastern wastes or in crystal caverns killing the rygorr orcs. And if your lucky you can camp Queen Drachnidd and get a crystalline robe off her.<br><br>                               Sincerely,<br>                             Turasiath Redmyst<br>                              Drinal server<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
